parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cylinder head can cause the engine to misfire, stall, or fail, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident.
The failure of the air conditioning compressor can cause the system to malfunction, leading to a loss of cooling and potentially causing discomfort or distraction while driving.
symptoms: Rattling or grinding noise from the compressor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage to the engine and potentially causing a loss of power or stalling.
Failure to adjust the valves at the recommended interval can cause engine problems, including misfiring, stalling, and burnt valves.
Transmission problems can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, potentially leading to an accident.
The sudden detachment of the sunroof visor while driving can cause a distraction, loss of control, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The sunroof visor detaches from the vehicle while driving
and can cause damage to the vehicle or surrounding objects.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering of windows can cause a distraction, loss of control, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Windows shatter or crack suddenly without any impact or apparent reason
causing a loud noise and potentially showering occupants with glass fragments.
